org.fluentjava.collections
Interface FluentList<E>

Type Parameters:
E - Type of elements
All Superinterfaces:
Collection<E>, Enumerable<E>, ExtendedCollection<E>, ExtendedIterable<E>, Iterable<E>, List<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ForwardingFluentList, Sequence
public interface FluentList<E>
extends List<E>, Enumerable<E>, ExtendedCollection<E>

List that has type safe toArray, and has a fluent interface on methods. Also, has more convenient methods to include and remove elements, and returns FluentLists where List would be returned. All Enumerable methods are also implemented.

FluentList<Object> flatten()
Returns a new list that is a one-dimensional flattening of this list (recursively). This means: for every element that is a list, extract its elements into the new array.
